DOCUMENT 3: Component Architecture & Data Flow V2  
Growth Velocity Calculator — Frontend Structure & Integration

Context: Existing Architecture  
The Growth Velocity Calculator already exists with:  
✅ Two-tab system at /vision-identity/growth-velocity  
Tab 1: Standard Calculator (Free \+ Pro)  
Tab 2: Scenario Builder (Pro only)  
✅ Tier gating logic (3 free calculations/day, unlimited for Pro)  
✅ Two Supabase tables: growth\_calculations and growth\_scenarios  
✅ Basic calculation engine and results display  
What V2 Updates:  
🔄 Enhanced input form (7 fields instead of 4\)  
🔄 New calculation engine (32 formulas, 6 pressure families)  
🔄 Enhanced results display (organized by pressure families)  
🆕 Real-time impact cards in Tab 2  
🆕 Visual comparison charts in Tab 2  
🆕 GPT synthesis with Agency Snapshot context

Page Architecture: Two Tabs, Distinct Purposes  
Tab 1: Standard Calculator (All Users)  
Purpose: Single scenario analysis with implications  
User Flow:  
Enter baseline (or auto-populate from Agency Snapshot)  
Set target revenue \+ timeframe  
Click "Calculate"  
See results \+ pressure family alerts  
Read GPT synthesis  
(Optional) Run again with different inputs (limited to 3/day for free users)  
Key Features:  
Single calculation run per interaction  
Results stored in growth\_calculations table  
GPT synthesis generated on each run  
No comparison functionality  
No sliders or presets

Tab 2: Scenario Builder (Pro Only)  
Purpose: Interactive scenario modeling with comparison  
User Flow:  
Baseline pre-populated from Agency Snapshot  
Select preset or adjust sliders manually  
See real-time impact cards update as sliders move  
Name and save scenario  
Build 2-3 different scenarios  
Compare scenarios side-by-side with visual charts  
Read GPT synthesis comparing scenarios  
Key Features:  
Real-time calculation (no "Calculate" button needed)  
Multiple saved scenarios per user  
Visual comparison charts (3 charts \+ scorecard)  
Scenario-specific GPT synthesis  
Unlimited runs for Pro users

